@node "Requirements" "Requirements"
TrapPrefs does not require much, you just need to have the following:

 1) Workbench 2.0+
 2) ReqTools library (© Nico Francois)
 3) @{"Magic User Interface" link "MUI" 0} v2.1 (will not work with 2.0 or before)
 4) TrapDoor v1.84 or v1.85 (© Maximilian Hantsch and Martin Laubach)

Optional
 1) Traplist library and a nodelist
 2) TIF (© Brian Jacobsen)
@endnode

@node "Locale" "Locale"
 TrapPrefs can be run in you prefered language.  To do this you need to copy
the appropriate trapprefs.catalog to you locale directory.  If your language
is not included, feel free to translate the included .ct file and send it to
me and I will send back to you the .catalog file.

NOTE: If you intend to translate TrapPrefs to your language, please read the
      included TrapPrefs.cd as there are some special instructions needed for
      proper translation.

NOTE:  As the number of registrations was very poor, only three, I will no
       longer be contacting the authors about updating the translations, as
       this takes too much time on my part and results in little gain.
       I will include the translations with the archive if they are sent to
       me however.  This will change if I start receiving more registrations.

