@node "Usage" "Usage"
TrapPrefs

All of the buttons, cycle gadgets, and button gadgets set one of TrapDoor's
keywords.  You just set the values as you want them they will automatically be
saved for you.  Please see TrapDoor.guide for a detailed explaination of each
option.

The Menu:
    Open    --  Loads a TrapDoor.cfg file into the prefs editor.
    Open As --  Opens a filerequester so that you can specify the name
                of the config to load.

    Save    --  Save the current config with the current name or as
                "Mail:TrapDoor.cfg" if none is specified
    Save As --  Opens a filerequester so that you can specify the name
                of the config to save.

    About   --  duh :-)

    Quit    --  Do I really need to tell you.

    Reset to Defaults  --  set all options to TrapDoor's default values.
                           NOTE: the cycle gadgets have the default setting
                                 in black, and the non default setting
                                 in white or the style specified with the
                                 COLOR tooltype

    Save TIF Labels --  the state of this checkmark menu item tells TrapPrefs
                        whether or not it should save the TIF labels.  This
                        will automatically be set if the loaded config
                        contains TIF labels, or you press return in one of
                        the TIF label string gadget.  NOTE: this is only
                        available in the registered version.

    Snapshot window --  when this is checked, TrapPrefs will save its window
                        position and size to disk when you quit.  NOTE: this
                        is only available in the registered version.

Loading configurations:
    When loading a configuration, if an error is discovered you will be
    notified of the error.  The error requester has three gadgets on it:
         Abort:    Stop loading the config, and restore previous config.
                   Note:  in order to restore the previous config the
                   directory T: must exist.
         Continue: Continue loading the config ignoring just this error
         Ignore:   Continue loading the config ignoring this and future
                   errors

The Window sizes:
    Clicking this gadget opens two windows, one representing the Log window
    and the other the Status window.  Just adjust the position and size as
    you want them and click either close gadget.

    If you change your mind just select 'Cancel' from the menu.

The Palette requester:
    If your screen mode is not Workbench or Active, a screen will open up
    as defined in your preferences with a palette requester on it.  Just
    adjust palette and click on OK to save the new palette.

    If you want to save a copy of the current WorkBench palette select
    'Use WorkBench Palette'.


The Modem Mode:
    This is were you set the default state for TrapDoor.
    There are the following three options:

    Answer     put TrapDoor in answer mode
    Call BOSS  make TrapDoor call your boss
    Call       with this option you need to fill in the 'Who' string.  This
               can be a node/point number or a phonenumber depending on if
               you have a nodelist installed.

Online help:
    Pressing 'HELP' with the cursor over a gadget will automaticall open up
    the appropriate page in TrapDoor.guide.  TrapDoor.guide must appear in
    your AmigaGuide search path.
    NOTE: Users of Workbench 2.x require MUI v2.3 in order for this to work.
@endnode

