@node "CLI" "Tooltypes and CLI options"
TrapPrefs supports the following tooltypes / cli options

Tooltype and/or CLI option

    CONFIG - name of TrapDoor config file to load at startup.  For example
             if you want TrapPrefs to automatically load
             "Mail:TrapDoor.cfg" when it is first run just add the
             following tooltype: 'CONFIG=Mail:TrapDoor.cfg'

Tooltypes only

    COLOR - color or style TrapPrefs should use to display non default
            options.  This option will be read even if TrapPrefs is started
            from the CLI.

            You can use any of the following:

            u    Set the soft style to underline.
            b    Set the soft style to bold.
            i    Set the soft style to italic
            n    Set the soft style back to normal.
           <n>   Use pen number n (2..9) as front pen. n must be a valid
                 DrawInfo pen as specified in "intuition/screens.h".

@endnode

