register users.

@endnode

@node "History" "History"
What has changed - most recent release is first.

v1.4d
    o Included my new addres in docs.
    o Found a small bug which would cause TrapPrefs to stop working when
      the new version of MUI is released (fixed)
    o A few other small bug fixes.

v1.4c
    o Added updated french catalog
    o Updated docs to show addition of UK registration site.
    o recompiled with SAS-C 6.55

v1.4b
    o Added a workaround to fix a bug in MUI, which causes enforcer hits
      when string gadgets are cleared.
    o If both the Boss and Call Who gadgets where blank, when loading a
      config the mode would be changed to Call Boss, no matter what was
      specified in the config.

v1.4a
    o Opps, TrapPrefs was not saving the log levels (fixed)
    o Added German and Italian catalogs

v1.4
    o ReqTools is no longer be used for the file requesters, TrapPrefs will
      now use the built in ASL functions of MUI.
      NOTE:  ReqTools is still required for the palette and screen mode
             requesters.
    o "True Color" screen modes were only being filtered if a DisplayID
      was already defined. (fixed)
    o Added PublicScreen selector to Public Screen string gadget
    o Completely changed the way TrapPrefs stores the current config in
      memory.
    o Added warning if config has been changed, but not saved.

v1.3b
    o Screen mode requester should no longer display the "True Color" modes
      when using graphics boards.  I'm not sure if this actually works as
      I don't have a gfx board to try it out.
    o Added Swedish, thanks to Magnus Holmgren for sending it to me.

v1.3a
    o 'Use workbench Palette' gadget was not being disabled correctly
      (fixed)
    o Fixed some memory leaks.

v1.3
    o Fixed small error in installer script.
    o The AutoOverScan and Interlace gadgets were not being disabled
      correctly when a DisplayID was specified (fixed)
    o Added French translation.
    o Moved 'Select DisplayID' to a popup gadget, and added 'Use Workbench
      Colors'
    o Added "Snapshot window" menu item, if this item is checked, the size
      and position of the window will be saved when you quit TrapPrefs
      (requires that C:Copy exist)
      - available only in the registered version
    o Added ability to save and edit the Labels for the gadgets on the
      TIF screen. - available only in the registered version
    o Screen Mode requester will now default to the current setting in
      the DisplayID - suggested by Steffen Salzmann

v1.2
    o About requester said 'TrapListPrefs' instead of 'TrapPrefs' (fixed)
      - reported by Steffen Salzmann
    o 'Abort' did not work correctly, requester would appear more than
       once (fixed)
      - reported by Steffen Salzmann
    o If you click on 'Abort', old config will be restored
      - suggested by Steffen Salzmann

v1.1
    o Localized a few more strings.  You will need TrapPrefs catalog v1.1
      for the new strings to be localized.
    o Fixed a few spelling errors
      - reported by Michael Berg
    o Added keyfile support, now when you register you will receive a
      keyfile to personalize your copy.  TrapPrefs itself still remains
      completely non crippled, however the TrapListPrefs will require the
      key file in order to work.
    o Added Abort and Continue options to error requesters when loading
      config.
      - suggested by Steffen Salzmann
    o Added hypertext link to TrapDoor.guide.  Now pressing HELP over a
      gadget will bring up the appropriate page in TrapDoor.guide.  NOTE:
      This feature requires that TrapDoor.guide be available in your
      AmigaGuide path.
      - requested by Piergiorgio Ghezzo
    o Added NodeList support, now if you have a nodelist TrapPrefs will
      read it and display the name and sysop of your boss.

v1.0
    o Fixed several enforcer hits when Resetting to Defaults
      - reported by Andre Schenk
    o Fixed an enforcer hit which magically appeared when I upgraded to
      MUI 2.2.  I believe the problem is with MUI v2.2 not TrapPrefs.
    o Dropped beta status.

0.9ß - 0.99ß
    o Anceint history
@endnode

