    o Make editors for SetConfig, SetPassword and other TrapDoor programs.
      This will depend on the response -- number of registrations I get :-)
    o Add "Save and Notify" to menus.  This would save the current config,
      and then tell TrapDoor, if it is running in memory, to read the new
      config.


    o Any good ideas you may have :-)
@endnode

@node "MUI" "MUI"

                          This application uses


                        MUI - MagicUserInterface

                (c) Copyright 1993/94 by Stefan Stuntz


MUI is a system to generate and maintain graphical user interfaces. With the
aid  of  a  preferences program, the user of an application has the ability to
customize the outfit according to his personal taste.

MUI is distributed as shareware. To obtain a complete package containing lots
of examples and more information about registration please look for a  file
called  "muiXXusr.lha"  (XX means the latest version number) on your local
bulletin boards or on public domain disks.

          If you want to register directly, feel free to send


                         DM 30.-  or  US$ 20.-

                                  to

                             Stefan Stuntz
                        Eduard-Spranger-Straße 7
                             80935 München
                                GERMANY
@endnode

@node "Questions" "Questions"
1. I get an error while reading the config if my dial strings
   contain '=' in it.

   This is a fault of AmigaDos.  I use ReadArgs() calls in order to read
   the config, and this function uses the '=' as a separator between key
   words and arguments.  The fix for this is very easy, enclose the string
   in quotes.  This is the way the examples in TrapDoor.guide are shown, and
   how TrapPrefs will save them.

   As an example use MODEMANSWER "~~~ATS7=25A|"
                 not MODEMANSWER ~~~ATS7=25A|   <- this will report an error.

2. I am using a white background for the cycle gadgets and I cannot read some
   of the options.

   The default options are shown in black and the non default are shown in
   white by TrapPrefs per default.  This can be changed by setting the
   tooltype @{"COLOR" link "CLI" 0}.  With this tooltype you can change the color, or even make
   the items bold or italic.

3. When I save my configuration, the labels I had set up for TIF are lost.

   The ability to load, edit, and save the TIF labels are only available in
   the registered version.  You will need to register in order to use these
   features.
@endnode

